The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses Fourier spectra of boolean functions, which is a topic in information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also makes use of concepts from data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG) in its analysis and protocols.
